Worse wildfires means more carbon in the atmosphere, more carbon in the atmosphere means worse wildfires.
At just 2-3 degrees of global warming, 1.4 billion people could face a dramatic decline in iron, leading to a potential global anemia epidemic.
On the basis of capitalism, where food is produced for profit rather than need, these deep contradictions are inevitable.
It is the practices they use to produce more food than we need that could make us all go hungry.
We need to entirely do away with capitalism and replace it with a system and society that is democratically planned.